main event: Five unidentified objects were sighted flying in formation at an estimated speed of 500-600 mph over Tioga, Colorado on June 9, 1949.
interesting points: The objects were observed in two echelons, two flying parallel followed by three which changed positions., The objects flew at an estimated altitude of 20,000 feet., The observer described the objects as round, approximately 2 feet in diameter, and brown in color., There was no evidence of exhaust or sound associated with the objects., Investigations revealed no known aerial research activity in the area at the time of the sighting.
witness description: a reliable farm hand, considered level-headed
